WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:04.210
We’ve all heard various sayings that decry
revenge as being a worthless act that’s

00:00:04.210 --> 00:00:05.859
beneath any civilized human being.

00:00:05.859 --> 00:00:08.820
“An eye for an eye leaves the whole world
blind” said Gandhi.

00:00:08.820 --> 00:00:12.700
“Before you embark on a journey of revenge,
dig two graves” said Confucius.

00:00:12.700 --> 00:00:16.750
“Two wrongs don’t make a right” said
your parents probably at some point during

00:00:16.750 --> 00:00:17.970
your childhood.

00:00:17.970 --> 00:00:23.130
But, whilst we can see their point with regards
to overt acts of revenge, there’s something

00:00:23.130 --> 00:00:27.519
to be said for the healing power of passive-aggressive
revenge.

00:00:27.519 --> 00:00:33.210
If you’re looking for ideas, look no further.

00:00:33.210 --> 00:00:34.400
