00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:39.160
British Royal Band Uses Star Wars to Insult
Saudi Monarch

00:00:39.160 --> 00:00:43.890
In 2007, King Abdullah of Saudi Arabia was
due to visit the UK for a royal engagement

00:00:43.890 --> 00:00:45.050
with Queen Elizabeth II.

00:00:45.050 --> 00:00:49.730
However, as the leader of a country where
torture is rife, human rights are routinely

00:00:49.730 --> 00:00:55.320
ignored, and governmental corruption is endemic,
it’s fair to say that this was a controversial

00:00:55.320 --> 00:00:56.320
outing.

00:00:56.320 --> 00:01:00.880
On arriving to meet the Queen, it’s a long-established
tradition that every monarch is greeted with

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:03.520
a performance by the British Welsh Guards.

00:01:03.520 --> 00:01:08.230
However, despite not wanting to perform for
such a character, they didn’t want to break

00:01:08.230 --> 00:01:09.290
years of protocol.

00:01:09.290 --> 00:01:13.690
So instead, when the King arrived, they greeted
him the most apropos song they could think

00:01:13.690 --> 00:01:18.440
of: the Imperial March, i.e. that song from
Star Wars that was commonly used to herald

00:01:18.440 --> 00:01:22.540
the arrival of supremely evil tyrants such
as Darth Vader.

00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:25.202
It’s not known whether the King understood
what was being played to him, but it’s easy

00:01:25.202 --> 00:01:28.890
to spot the people in that video we linked
who are trying their best to keep a straight

00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:34.780
face whilst royal protocol trashes a guy’s
reputation in the eyes of the world.

00:01:34.780 --> 00:01:35.780
9.

00:01:35.780 --> 00:01:37.570
Arnold Schwarzenegger Makes a Sweary Poem

00:01:37.570 --> 00:01:42.630
Arnold Schwarzenegger is a man of many talents:
bodybuilder, actor, politician, and more recently

00:01:42.630 --> 00:01:43.630
a poet.

00:01:43.630 --> 00:01:48.820
In a 2010 letter vetoing a bill authored by
Democratic assemblymen Tom Ammiano, readers

00:01:48.820 --> 00:01:54.640
noticed a hidden message from Schwarzenegger
in the left-hand margin: the words “F**k

00:01:54.640 --> 00:01:55.640
You.”

00:01:55.640 --> 00:01:59.590
Coincidentally, several weeks beforehand,
Ammiano had heckled The Governator, openly

00:01:59.590 --> 00:02:03.970
accusing him of lying about his policies during
his time in office, all whilst the latter

00:02:03.970 --> 00:02:06.780
was giving a speech at a Democratic Party
fundraiser.

00:02:06.780 --> 00:02:10.480
When the message was revealed, Arnold suggested
that the whole thing was just a coincidence

00:02:10.480 --> 00:02:18.250
and that “when you do so many vetoes, something
like this is bound to happen,” he said knowingly

00:02:18.250 --> 00:02:20.010
with a wink (probably).

00:02:20.010 --> 00:02:21.010
