00:02:21.010 --> 00:02:22.980
Ronald Emmerich Hits Back at Ebert and Siskel

00:02:22.980 --> 00:02:26.540
Movie director Ronald Emmerich was really
suffering at the hands of the critics.

00:02:26.540 --> 00:02:29.870
Well, two critics: Gene Siskel and Robert
Ebert.

00:02:29.870 --> 00:02:34.270
They hadn’t been too kind in their reviews
of Universal Soldier, Stargate, and Independence

00:02:34.270 --> 00:02:39.060
Day, so Emmerich decided to give them a part
in his next movie, Godzilla.

00:02:39.060 --> 00:02:43.620
Casting two actors who bear a remarkable similarity
to the pair, he created the characters of

00:02:43.620 --> 00:02:49.870
Mayor Ebert, an argumentative, meddling buffoon,
and Gene, the mayor’s sycophantic lacky.

00:02:49.870 --> 00:02:54.240
However, despite Emmerich’s blind hatred
of the pair, they made it out of the movie

00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:58.750
alive, leaving Ebert openly puzzled puzzled
about why they hadn’t been eaten or squashed

00:02:58.750 --> 00:02:59.750
underfoot.

00:02:59.750 --> 00:03:00.750
