00:03:00.750 --> 00:03:02.620
Lord Byron Buys a Bear

00:03:02.620 --> 00:03:07.420
In 1805, Lord Byron was starting his first
year at the prestigious Cambridge Trinity

00:03:07.420 --> 00:03:12.340
College and requested to the administration
that he be able to bring his dog to live with

00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:13.340
him.

00:03:13.340 --> 00:03:16.599
On receiving the request, the college flat-out
denied it, citing a rule which prohibited

00:03:16.599 --> 00:03:17.850
dogs on campus.

00:03:17.850 --> 00:03:21.820
As a result, Byron then went out and did what
many of us would do when faced with such a

00:03:21.820 --> 00:03:26.319
petty, obstructive rule: buy a freakin’
bear.

00:03:26.319 --> 00:03:29.920
On returning to the college, he was asked
to kindly get the animal off the premises.

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:33.760
Byron agreed to do so, as soon as the college
showed him the rule which prohibited bears

00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:34.760
from living on-campus.

00:03:34.760 --> 00:03:39.190
As they couldn’t, the bear stayed with Byron
all throughout his studies.

00:03:39.190 --> 00:03:40.190
