00:07:27.020 --> 00:07:28.939
South Korea Blasts K-Pop at the North

00:07:28.939 --> 00:07:34.440
It’s fair to say that the relationship between
North Korea and South Korea is somewhat fragile.

00:07:34.440 --> 00:07:39.690
Over the years, they’ve engaged in numerous
gun battles and psychological campaigns, despite

00:07:39.690 --> 00:07:43.629
being separated by one of the most-heavily
armed borders in the world.

00:07:43.629 --> 00:07:46.990
In 2010, however, the situation was direr
than ever.

00:07:46.990 --> 00:07:50.409
In March of that year, the North Koreans sank
the ROKS Cheonan, a Navy ship belonging to

00:07:50.409 --> 00:07:51.409
the South.

00:07:51.409 --> 00:07:54.225
This was soon followed by an artillery attack
on the island of Yeonpyeong, an island situated

00:07:54.225 --> 00:07:56.129
well within South Korea’s territory.

00:07:56.129 --> 00:07:58.749
You can imagine that the South launched a
blistering counter-attack.

00:07:58.749 --> 00:08:00.379
And they did.

00:08:00.379 --> 00:08:04.819
In June, they set up their own FM radio station,
through which they blasted the North Koreans

00:08:04.819 --> 00:08:09.789
with the sickly-sweet sounds of Korean pop
music, also referred to as K-Pop.

00:08:09.789 --> 00:08:13.899
Predictably, the North didn’t appreciate
this lesson in musical history, and threatened

00:08:13.899 --> 00:08:16.629
all-out war unless the transmissions were
turned off.

00:08:16.629 --> 00:08:17.629
They weren’t.

00:08:17.629 --> 00:08:20.849
We like to think that the South’s response
to this was just to turn the dials all the

00:08:20.849 --> 00:08:26.530
way up to 11, and rock North Korea’s face
so hard that they completely forget to follow

00:08:26.530 --> 00:08:28.770
through on their threat.

00:08:28.770 --> 00:08:29.770
1.

00:08:29.770 --> 00:08:32.700
Gustav Klimt Bares Some Painted Flesh

00:08:32.700 --> 00:08:37.550
Gustav Klimt is the master painter responsible
for renowned works such as “The Kiss”

00:08:37.550 --> 00:08:39.440
and “Adele Bloch-Bauer I.”

00:08:39.440 --> 00:08:44.660
He specialized in drawings of the female form,
AKA mass nudity.

00:08:44.660 --> 00:08:48.770
So it’s strange that, after being commissioned
by the University of Vienna to paint human

00:08:48.770 --> 00:08:53.830
representations of Philosophy, Jurisprudence,
and Medicine, each design was refused on the

00:08:53.830 --> 00:08:55.960
grounds that it was “pornographic.”

00:08:55.960 --> 00:08:59.850
Like the school didn’t know what they were
getting themselves into.

00:08:59.850 --> 00:09:03.510
Unwilling to appeal to the conservative masses
any longer, he painted “Nuda Veritas”

00:09:03.510 --> 00:09:07.750
in response, which depicts a young, naked
woman holding a mirror to the face of the

00:09:07.750 --> 00:09:08.750
viewer.

00:09:08.750 --> 00:09:12.860
Also, above this figure is a quote by Friedrich
Schiller stating “If you cannot please everyone

00:09:12.860 --> 00:09:16.670
with your deeds and your art, please only
a few.

00:09:16.670 --> 00:09:18.680
To please many is bad.”

00:09:18.680 --> 00:09:26.370
As with all great art, words are never enough
to describe it, so here’s a link to it if

00:09:26.370 --> 00:09:27.720
you’re not in work or school.

